<HEADLINE>
HOLMES WAS A SUPREMELY QUOTABLE MAN
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: Supreme Court Justice William Brennan liked the following
William Butler Yeats quotation: ``Did you see an old woman going
down the path?'' asks Bridget. ``No, I did not,'' replies Patrick,
who came into the house just after the old woman left it. ``But I
saw a young girl, and she had the walk of a queen.'' What does it
refer to? _ C.P.H., Arlington, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: It comes from the Yeats play ``Cathleen ni Houlihan.'' One of
the many people Brennan quoted it to was Nat Hentoff, who wrote
about the conversation in a 1997 ``Washington Post'' column.
</P>
<P>
   ``His conviction remained that the living, evolving Constitution
_ not frozen in time more than 200 years ago _ will surely
rejuvenate liberty in the decades ahead,'' Hentoff wrote.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Where can I write to the foundation that actor Jimmy Smits
established? _ J.R., Fort Worth, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: Write to the National Hispanic Foundation for the Arts,
Georgetown Place, 1101 30th St., N.W., Suite 500, Washington, DC
20007.
</P>
<P>
   The foundation was created in 1997 to foster opportunities in
the entertainment industry for Hispanic actors and executives.
Toward that cause, it is co-sponsoring a Sept. 22 forum in
Washington with the FCC and President Clinton's Initiative on Race.
</P>
<P>
   You can send e-mail to the foundation by visiting its World Wide
Web site at www.incacorp.com/nhfa.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Is the group Confederate Railroad still in business? _ D.,
Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A: The group has more than 60 concert appearances scheduled for
the rest of 1998, according to its Web site at
www.confederaterailroad.net.
</P>
<P>
   Railroad, winners of a ``best new vocal group'' award in 1993,
has a fan club at Box 128185, Nashville, TN 37212-8185. Yearly
membership costs $12 in the United States and $15 in Canada.  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com) &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
