(EDS: Accompanies CARS-WILLIAMS-COLUMN) 
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   At A Glance: 1998 Lexus ES 300 sedan
</P>
<P>
   The Package: Midsize, four-door, five-passenger, V-6 powered,
front-drive, near-luxury sedan, built on the same chassis and with
the same drivetrain as the six-cylinder Toyota Camry.
</P>
<P>
   Highlights: Outstanding quality; powerful V-6 engine; superquiet
ride; new side-impact air bags for driver and front passenger for
1998.
</P>
<P>
   Negatives: Back seat is tight for three adults; price is about
$5,000 higher than that of a comparably equipped and nearly
identical Camry.
</P>
<P>
   Major competitors: BMW 3-series, Mercedes-Benz C-class, Audi A4,
Acura TL, Infiniti I30, Oldsmobile Aurora, Mazda Millennia S, Volvo
S70, Saab 9-3, Cadillac Catera.
</P>
<P>
   EPA fuel economy: 19 miles per gallon city, 26 highway.
</P>
<P>
   Base price: $30,790 plus $495 transportation.
</P>
<P>
   Price as tested: Not provided.
</P>
<P>
   On The Road rating: A-minus.
</P>
<P>
   _
</P>
<P>
   (Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide
Web: www.star-telegram.com)
