   YUGO-KOSOVO (Sedlare, Serbia) _ Out of sight of the diplomats,
foreign monitors and aid workers in the Serbian province of Kosovo
there were thousands of new refugees Friday, fleeing a military
offensive the government decreed was over a day ago. By Mike
O'Connor.
</P>
<P>
   JAPAN-OBUCHI (Tokyo) _ Keizo Obuchi, the new prime minister,
pledged to fix Japan's economy for the sake of the nation, Asia and
the world but said he was not a ``superman'' who could solve all
the problems on his own. By Stephanie Strom.
</P>
