r l &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-LIFESTYLE-BUDGET-LADN     07-31 0262
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LIFESTYLE-BUDGET-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
.
</HEADLINE>
  
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following stories
today for use by NYTimes News Service clients. They will move in
the ``l'' lifestyle news file. For questions, contact Jimmy Johnson
at the Daily News, (818) 713-3695. 
. 
VAMPIRE (Los Angeles) _ The homeless man nestled himself on a hard
bench at Glendale City Hall, molding his modest belongings into a
makeshift pillow to better his view of two dozen people, many
dressed in business attire, lurking underneath the courtyard's
arches. These strange creatures circled the gurgling fountain; they
talked in groups, often in hushed voices. This is a vampire game,
where participants take on guises of vampires, werewolfs and other
creatures of the night. By Heesun Wee. 
. 
The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following stories
today for use by NYTimes News Service clients. They will move in
the ``e'' entertainment news file. For questions, contact Jimmy
Johnson at the Daily News, (818) 713-3695. 
. 
IAN-MUSIC (Los Angeles) _ Los Angeles is burning up, but the
transplanted Brit looks cool. Relaxed. As if the Huntington
Library's shady outdoor cafe were Ian Whitcomb's natural habitat
and he'd been reared in this desert inferno instead of in mild,
moist Surrey, England. Of course, Whitcomb has had nearly 30 years
to adapt to Southern California's endless summers, ever since a
boyhood infatuation with comic books, Hollywood movies and rock 'n'
roll first lured him to America. By Reed Johnson. 
. 

