<HEADLINE>
THIS WEEK'S BUSINESS EVENTS CALENDAR  
 (FOR RELEASE SUNDAY, AUG. 2) 
</HEADLINE>
   (af)  
 c.1998 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   MONDAY: The Commerce Department reports on personal income and
spending for June. Forecasts call for increases of 0.2 percent in
personal income and 0.4 percent in spending.
</P>
<P>
   The National Association of Purchasing Management releases its
purchasing managers index for July. An easing of 0.7, to 48.9, is
expected.
</P>
<P>
   The Commerce Department reports on construction spending for
June. An increase of 0.8 percent is expected.
</P>
<P>
   Chrysler reports on July auto sales.
</P>
<P>
   TUESDAY: The Conference Board reports on the leading economic
indicators for June. A drop of 0.1, to 105.1 on the index, is
expected.
</P>
<P>
   WEDNESDAY: Ford and General Motors report July auto sales.
</P>
<P>
   The Federal Reserve's ``beige book'' report on regional economic
conditions is due.
</P>
<P>
   THURSDAY: The Labor Department reports weekly claims for
unemployment insurance.
</P>
<P>
   The Commerce Department reports on factory orders for June. A
decline of 0.2 percent is forecast.
</P>
<P>
   FRIDAY: The Labor Department releases its employment report for
July. The unemployment rate is expected to hold even at 4.5
percent.
</P>
<P>
   The Federal Reserve reports on consumer credit for June. An
increase of $3.2 billion is expected.
</P>
<P>
   SATURDAY: Microsoft faces Federal District Judge Thomas Penfield
on antitrust charges brought by the Justice Department and 20
states.
</P>
