   UPS _A year after the bruising strike at UPS, Teamsters again
took up their posts outside the gates of company distribution hubs
Friday. This time they were handing out flyers, not striking. But
workers are voicing complaints remarkably similar to those they had
before the strike. (Kempner, Atlanta Journal-Constitution) ETA 8
p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   DELTA _ Flight 284 from Atlanta to West Palm Beach, a seemingly
quick trip taking 1 hour and 43 minutes, has the worst on-time
record of any flight tracked by the DOT last year. In one month,
the flight was late 29 of 31 days. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
ETA 8 p.m. ET.
</P>
<P>
   DOLPHINS-CAMP _ DAVIE _ This is the definition of an optimist.
You are an NFL rookie. Training camp is 10 days old and you are in
the coach's doghouse. In fact, you figure you have ``the biggest
chain in the whole doghouse'' strapped to your neck. And you see
this as a good thing. This is Miami Dolphins running back John
Avery's view of the saga that has unfolded ever since he strained
his right hamstring Sunday during an intrasquad scrimmage. (Woods,
Palm Beach Post) MOVED.
</P>
<P>
   ARCHDEACON-COLUMN _ Tens of thousands of fans waited almost four
hours until the track dried enough for qualifying and Ernie Irvan
won the pole. That kind of not-so-dry devotion tells you a lot
about why NASCAR is the fastest growing spectator sport in the
country. (Archdeacon, Dayton Daily News) MOVED.
</P>
