 &QL; 
 &QL; 
AUTO-REVIEW (Undated) - Full-size, luxury sport-utility vehicles
have become major cash cows for automakers. Thus, the Denali. This
represents the first foray for GMC, formerly GM's utility and
work-truck division, into the big world of luxury trucks. The luxo
version of the Yukon, Denali is named after Denali National Park
and Preserve in Alaska and is the Native American name for the
south peak of Mount McKinley, which is in the park, natch. The fact
that the Denali looks as big as a mountain sitting among other cars
and SUVs is coincidental. By BOB GOLFEN. Story moved in the ``L''
category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
