 &HT;    On deck: St. Louis Cardinals
 &HT;    By Thomas Stinson
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   When: 1:15 p.m.
</P>
<P>
   Where: Turner Field.
</P>
<P>
   TV/radio: WAGA-5, WSB 750-AM.
</P>
<P>
   Probable starting pitchers: LHP Tom Glavine (14-4, 2.68; 11-4,
3.85 lifetime vs. Cardinals) vs. LHP Kent Mercker (6-8, 5.94; 0-2,
6.35).
</P>
<P>
   Notes: Glavine has lost just once since June 18, a span of seven
starts in which he has given up more than two runs just once. He
worked through the seventh inning in each of his last eight games
and was denied No. 15 after giving up an eighth-inning run in
Cincinnati on Monday. He has been successful through the years
against the Cardinals but will remember the last time he faced
them, when he gave up a two-run homer to Mark McGwire in the ninth,
on Aug. 15 last year. The Braves lost 3-2 in 12 innings. Mercker
makes his fourth start against the Braves and his second at Turner
Field. The Braves beat him twice last year as a Cincinnati Red,
accumulating 24 hits and 12 runs in 17 innings against him. The
only current Brave to homer off Mercker is Javy Lopez. Mercker has
won just once in his last eight starts, the win coming his last
time out in a 3-1 decision at Colorado. He allowed one run on five
hits over five innings before he was forced from the game because
of dizziness. In his five previous starts, Mercker had given up 22
runs in 22 1/3 innings.
</P>
