   (NYT28) PARK CITY, Mont. -- July 31, 1998 -- CAPITOL-MONTANA,
7-31 -- Vistas like this, of the Yellowstone River near Park City,
draw a lot of people to Big Sky Country. But they also attract
runaway loners as troubled as the Unabomber and Russell Weston Jr.,
the man charged with killing two Capitol police officers. (Larry
Mayer/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT27) WASHINGTON -- July 31, 1998 -- CAPITOL-SHOOTING-2, 7-31
-- Capitol Hill Police officers comfort each other following the
funeral of slain Capitol Police Officer Jacob Joseph Chestnut in
Arlington National Cemetery. ``It was not the way he died that made
him a hero, but the way that he lived,'' Gary Albrecht, chief of
the Capitol Police, tells the more than 3,000 people gathered here
to mourn. (Fred R. Conrad/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT26) WASHINGTON -- July 31, 1998 -- CAPITOL-SHOOTING-1, 7-31
-- Gary Albrecht, chief of the Capitol Police, comforts slain
Capitol Police Officer Jacob Joseph Chestnut's son Joseph, while
his widow, Wen Ling, holds the flag that draped the coffin during
his funeral in Arlington National Cemetery. ``It was not the way he
died that made him a hero, but the way that he lived,'' Albrecht
tells the more than 3,000 people gathered here to mourn. (Fred R.
Conrad/New York Times Photo)
