<P>
   (NYT23) BEIJING, China -- July 31, 1998 -- BEIJING-OPERA, 7-31
-- Chinese leaders say that by 2002 this lot across the street from
the Great Hall of the People will be filled with a $400 million
opera house complex. The first plans to build it were made 40 years
ago, then buried, revived, debated, revoked and almost forgotten in
a tangled bureaucracy. ``That's the torturous and winding path of
China,'' says Wu Zuqiang, a composer and advocate of the opera
house. (Seth Faison/New York Times Photo) *LITE
</P>
<P>
   (NYT22) GREENWICH, Conn. -- July 31, 1998 --
MARTHA-STEWART-STUDIES, 7-31 -- Like Madonna a decade ago, Martha
Stewart is today a piping hot offering on the cultural- studies
smorgasbord. In the last few years, about two dozen scholars across
the United States and Canada have trained their gaze on the woman
often described as the doyenne of domesticity. ``I don't think
she's building her advice about bourgeois taste around issues of
family,'' one scholar says of Ms. Stewart. (Joyce Dopkeen/New York
Times Photo)
</P>
