A3280 &Cx1f; tad-z
u s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BRTRADE-COX     07-31 0461
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BRTRADE-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Johnson left out of dealing
 &HT;    By I.J. Rosenberg
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA -- The trades came fast and furious Friday night and
should have a big impact not only on the rest of the regular season
but also in October.
</P>
<P>
   With the deadline approaching at midnight, all of baseball was
waiting to see where Seattle Mariners starter Randy Johnson would
land.
</P>
<P>
   Several teams were still in the hunt, the front-runners being
the Yankees and Indians. But the Dodgers were making a late run, as
were the Astros and, reportedly, the Braves. Another possibility
had Mo Vaughn going to the Mets for catcher Mike Piazza. The White
Sox were dangling third baseman Robin Ventura. Tampa Bay was
talking about dealing Roberto Hernandez, while the Cardinals,
involved in the first deals of the day, were considering moving
outfielder Brian Jordan.
</P>
<P>
   But there were plenty of early deals with the Texas Rangers
perhaps gaining the most. By 8 p.m. there were already seven deals.
</P>
<P>
   The Rangers were major players, getting starter Todd Stottlemyre
and shortstop Royce Clayton from the Cardinals and third baseman
Todd Zeile from the Marlins. Clayton and Zeile give Texas a better
left side of the infield while Stottlemyre (9-9, 3.51 ERA) is
having the best year of his career. The Cardinals got third base
prospect Fernando Tatis, disappointing right-hander Darren Oliver
and a player to be named. The Rangers had a chance to get Roger
Clemens from Toronto but did not want to give up outfielder Rusty
Greer.
</P>
<P>
   ``There's no doubt our direction with what we've done today is
to win our division and go beyond,'' Rangers general manager Doug
Melvin said.
</P>
<P>
   The Dodgers, with general manager Tommy Lasorda talking boldly
about making the playoffs, acquired second baseman Mark
Grudzielanek and starting pitcher Carlos Perez from the Expos for
second baseman Wilton Guerrero and three prospects. The Braves had
been interested in Grudzielanek.
</P>
<P>
   The Giants, who picked up Jose Mesa and Shawon Dunston last
week, continued upgrading, getting outfielder Ellis Burks from the
Rockies for outfielder Darryl Hamilton, minor leaguer James Stoops
and a player to be named.Making a second-half run at the wildcard,
the Orioles picked up starter Juan Guzman from Toronto for pitcher
Nerio Rodriguez and minor league outfielder Shannon Carter.
</P>
<P>
   The Mets acquired starter Willie Blair and catcher Jorge
Fabregas from the Diamondbacks for outfielder Bernard Gilkey and
minor leaguer Nelson Figueroa. Why would the Mets acquire a catcher
when they already have Piazza and Todd Hundley? Many felt this deal
would lead to another one involving Piazza.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
